                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <b>B. External Supply and Extract</b>
                            – The external venting points can go through a wall or a roof
                            depending on the project’s limitations - always look to keep a distance of 1.5m
                            between these or use a
                            specialised wall cowl designed for close proximity venting.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <b>C. Thermal piping from the machine to the Manifolds</b>
                            – Between your machine and manifolds we advise
                            to use thermally insulated ducting - in this run if your machine does not come with
                            silencers built in we will
                            always include silencers in the kit - in this run is where the silencers will be
                            placed.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <b>D. Manifolds or Distribution boxes</b>
                            – You will need 2 of these depending on your project 1 will be
                            solely for extracting the stale, humid and warm air from your Kitchens, Bathrooms
                            etc and one will be for
                            supplying the fresh air back into the building.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <b>E. Semi Rigid Radial pipe</b>
                            – We typically use a 75mm semi rigid Anti-Bacterial and Anti-static pipe -
                            Normally there will be 2 of these pipes running to each plenum.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            <b>F. Plenum and Valves</b>
                            – The 2 radial pipes will run into the plenum which will then go down at a 90
                            degree angle into a 125mm opening this is where you will then place your valve into
                            after trimming flush -
                            The valve will be the only thing you see once the fitting is completed.
                        </p>

